<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 04 at 2:11PM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...ICY CONDITIONS DEVELOPING FOR THE AFTERNOON COMMUTE...
Temperatures were or are expected to drop into the upper 20s to
around 30, through 4pm with light freezing rain and
drizzle developing across the region.
The freezing rain may coat roadways with a thin layer of ice that
may be undetectable. Please use extreme caution, especially on
bridges, overpasses and around curves. Allow plenty of stopping
distance and avoid braking suddenly.
Locations impacted include...
Newark, Jersey City, Yonkers, Paterson, Stamford, New Rochelle,
Flushing, Passaic, White Plains, Wayne, Mott Haven, Hoboken,
Bloomfield, East Tremont and Hackensack.
A Winter Weather Advisory is in effect for the area. Please monitor
local media outlets and the National Weather Service for further
statements.</description>
